	<Task>
		<Title>Run Microsoft Meltdown and Spectre Detection Tool - Windows</Title>
		<Description><![CDATA[<P>This Task runs a powershell script created by Microsoft to determine machines' exposure to the Meltdown and Spectre vulnerabilities and provide suggested actions. Running this task will create a text file with the script's results. You will have to activate the paired analysis in order to collect that data.</P>
<P>More information from Microsoft on the script and recommendations are available at the following links for servers ( <A href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4072698/windows-server-guidance-to-protect-against-the-speculative-execution">https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4072698/windows-server-guidance-to-protect-against-the-speculative-execution</A> ) and workstations ( <A href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4073119/windows-client-guidance-for-it-pros-to-protect-against-speculative-exe">https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4073119/windows-client-guidance-for-it-pros-to-protect-against-speculative-exe</A> ).</P>]]></Description>
		<Relevance>windows of operating system</Relevance>
		<Relevance><![CDATA[exists (it as string as version) whose(it >= "2") of values "PowerShellVersion" of keys "PowerShellEngine" of keys ((it as string) of maximum of (it as integer) of names of keys of keys "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\PowerShell" of (x64 registries;x32 registries)) of keys "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\PowerShell" of (x64 registries;x32 registries)]]></Relevance>
		<Relevance><![CDATA[not exists (now - it) whose(it < 6*hour) of modification times of files "results_PS_SpeculationControl.txt" of folders "Logs" of folders "__Global" of data folders of client]]></Relevance>
